==Setting up==
Make sure you have around 70% run energy before you head into the lair. You'll need to do some running to attract the [[Kalphite Guardian]]s and the [[Kalphite Queen]], and running out of run energy can force you to tank more hits from the Queen herself. Since you probably don't have the [[elite Desert Diary]] done, you'll have to take the long way around - walking this part helps conserve run energy.

It is advisable to watch a video on the below method on setting up the Kalphite Queen, such as [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QrP4QMYSPOA this one].

Turn on [[Protect from Melee]] as you go into the lair and attract the two [[Kalphite Guardian]]s near the entrance. Run back to the entrance rope and stand two tiles to the south of it - this should cause the two Guardians to stand one behind the other in a line. With this done, turn on [[Protect from Missiles]] and find the Kalphite Queen to attract her attention (do not attack the Kalphite Queen if using a bone dagger as your special weapon), then run back to the entrance and stand two tiles west and one tile north of the entrance rope. If done correctly, the two Kalphite Guardians and the Kalphite Queen will be stood in a line facing you, with the Kalphite Queen out of attack range. If the Kalphite Queen gets stuck on the cocoon in the middle after attracting her attention, walk diagonally south-west 2 tiles and then back to release her.

With the Guardians and the queen in a line, turn on [[Protect from Missiles]] then run 3 tiles south of the Kalphite's Queen south-western tile, then immediately run under her. The Guardians should now position themselves to trap the queen against the cocoon in the middle, and she is unable to move to attack to you while stood under her.

==Flinching==
With the Kalphite Queen stuck, all you have to do is flinch the Kalphite Queen with your melee weapon until she is dead. It is highly recommended to summon thralls, as they will significantly increase kill speed, as they will be able to do damage while you are waiting for your next attack.

Due to the Kalphite Queen's attack speed, you can attack once every 10 ticks without her retaliating against you.
==After the kill==
After the kill, the flinching safespot will need to be set up again.

If playing as an ironman, simply leave the lair and re-enter, as this will reset the instance to a fresh state.

If playing on a standard account, the Kalphite workers which spawned during the fight will need to be defeated before trying to set up the flinching safespot again, or you may choose to hop worlds to look for a fresh lair.

