==Inventory Setups==
===Pre-Elite Desert Diary===
Players may need to complete up to 256 killcount before receiving the [[kq head]] or [[Kq head (tattered)|tattered kq head]] to complete the Elite Desert Diary and unlock the shortcut at 86 [[Agility]]. Until then, it is generally better to maximise kills per trip by minimising extra switches and/or flinching the boss. 

===Post-Elite Desert Diary===
With the desert elite diary completed, it becomes much more beneficial to focus on high damage output as it is quick to return to the lair after restoring stats at your POH with the agility shortcut. This method capitalises on maximum [[Melee]] and [[Ranged]]/[[Magic]] attack bonuses, and every kill will start with full health, prayer, and special attack.

Having a [[Kalphite]] [[Slayer task]] to use the [[Slayer helmet]] is strongly recommended for saving an inventory space and significantly boosting damage.

With the recoil enabled, [[ring of suffering (ri)]] deals a lot of damage due to the frequency and severity of the Queen's attacks. An [[ultor ring]] with a scythe or partisan of breaching are an exception due to their unique damage scaling, but the suffering provides extra damage during both phases and when not using melee.
If you take too much damage, step under the boss to heal. Otherwise, heal during the phase transition.
